China's Li makes history with French Open title
2011-06-04 15:30:03 GMT
PARIS â€“ Li Na became the first Chinese player to win a Grand Slam singles title on Saturday when she defeated defending champion Francesca Schiavone 6-4, 7-6 (7/0) in the French Open final.Britain's long-time No. 1 player Anne Keothavong said on BBC Two: "It was a great tie-break by Li Na and credit to her -- she's a great champion, a great player and deserves this. She got tight and nervous and we saw her vent her frustrations but she kept it together at the end. Schiavone is a warrior and Li Na still had to close it out, she did a great job." "I'd like to thank Schiavone for a great two weeks," Champion Li Na said after the match. Runner-up Francesca Schiavone told reporters that, "Today was really tough. I have to say congratulations to Li Na - this year she has grown up so much. To kiss the clay every day is something from my heart and I will always remember this." (Agencies)
